-- Royce Discusses Her Book ‘The Empress Has No Clothes’ (Audio)
-- B y
-- 2013-11-23T00:25:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-23/royce-discusses-her-book-the-empress-has-no-clothes-audio-.html
 Joyce M. Roche, Avon's the first 
African American female vice president, former chief operating 
officer of Carson Products Company, and former chief executive 
officer of Girls Inc., and currently a board member at five 
Fortune 500 companies, discusses her book, "The  Empress Has No 
Clothes: Conquering Self-Doubt to Embrace Success."  She 
discusses "climbing the corporate ladder" and continually 
doubting her success, a prime example of "the imposter syndrome"
which women, and men, often experience.  Royce spoke with 
Bloomberg's  Kathleen Hays  and Vonnie Quinn on Nov. 21 on 
 Bloomberg Radio 's "The Hays Advantage" at Bloomberg's The Year 
Ahead 2014 conference in Chicago.   (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 10:39
 